'''''ESPN MLS ExtraTime 2002''''', or '''''ESPN MLS ExtraTime''''', is a [[sports game|sports]] [[video game]] released in 2002 by [[Konami]].<ref name="gamefaqs2002">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamefaqs.com/xbox/560625-espn-mls-extratime-2002/data |title=ESPN MLS ExtraTime 2002 Release Information for Xbox |publisher=GameFAQs |date=2002-03-27 |accessdate=2013-01-10}}</ref> It is available for [[GameCube]], [[Xbox (console)|Xbox]], and [[PlayStation 2]].<ref name="gamefaqs2002"/> [[Clint Mathis]] is on the cover. The [[PlayStation 2]] version was released seven months after ''[[ESPN MLS GameNight]]'' on the [[PlayStation (console)|PlayStation]], with the [[GameCube]] and [[Xbox (console)|Xbox]] versions coming out 11 months after that. ''MLS ExtraTime'' was the last in the series as the [[Major League Soccer|MLS]] sold its video game license to [[EA Sports]]' [[FIFA (video game series)|''FIFA'' series]].

==Reception==
The game received positive reviews from critics. There is an average score of 70.8% for the GameCube version of the game at GameRankings based on 8 reviews from various sites. The average for the Xbox version is lower at 70.1%.

