== 2015 == The '''2015 Caribbean Combine''' was held between January 2–5, 2015 in [[Bayamón, Puerto Rico]]. The combine took place at the facilities of [[Bayamón FC]], including [[Juan Ramón Loubriel Stadium]], and featured matches with local clubs.<ref name="Second Caribbean Player Combine">{{cite web|title=MLS, Caribbean Football Union to host second Caribbean Player Combine in Puerto Rico|url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/news/article/2014/11/25/mls-caribbean-football-union-host-second-caribbean-player-combine-puerto-ric|publisher=Major League Soccer|accessdate=25 November 2014}}</ref> For the combine, 19 players representing 17 associations from the region were invited.<ref name="announces 19 players">{{cite web|title=Major League Soccer announces 19 players invited to Caribbean Combine|url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/news/article/2015/01/01/major-league-soccer-announces-19-players-invited-caribbean-combine|publisher=Major League Soccer|accessdate=6 January 2015}}</ref> Following the Caribbean Combine, only [[Jean Carlos Lopez Moscoso]] of the Dominican Republic was invited to the MLS Combine.<ref name="2015 Generation adidas">{{cite web|title=Major League Soccer announces 2015 Generation adidas class|url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/news/article/2015/01/08/major-league-soccer-announces-2015-generation-adidas-class|publisher=Major League Soccer|accessdate=9 January 2015}}</ref> No players from the Caribbean combine were selected as Lopez was not taken in any of the four rounds of the draft.<ref name="2015 MLS SuperDraft">{{cite web|title=2015 MLS SuperDraft Draft Tracker|url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/superdraft/2015/tracker|publisher=Major League Soccer|accessdate=21 January 2015}}</ref>
