==2016== The 2016 edition of the MLS Caribbean Combine was held on three different islands at different times, unlike previous years in which it was held at a central location. Players were invited to specific host islands based up their country of origin. Twenty four players were invited to each location for a total of 72 players, a significant increase over previous years. The reason for decentralizing the combine was to make it easier for more nations to participate.<ref name="2015/2016">{{cite web|title=2015 MLS Combine to be held across three islands|url=http://cfufootball.org/index.php/men-s-u20/9763-2015-mls-combine-to-be-held-across-three-islands|publisher=Caribbean Football Union|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>
===Hosting and known players=== *'''Saint Kitts and Nevis''' hosted players from Anguilla, Antigua and Barbuda, British Virgin Islands, Cayman Islands, Jamaica, Montserrat, Puerto Rico, Turks and Caicos, and the United States Virgin Islands from 13 December to 16 December<ref name="2015/2016"/><ref name="St. Kitts for the first time">{{cite web|title=Major League Soccer try-outs in St. Kitts for the first time|url=http://miyvue.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=24934:opportunity-for-local-footballers-in-federation-hosted-mls-combine&catid=42:rokstories&Itemid=109|publisher=miyvue.com|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref> at the [[Warner Park Sporting Complex]].<ref name="raise the level">{{cite web|last1=Abel|first1=Jermine|title=MLS Combine expected to raise the level of local|url=http://www.thestkittsnevisobserver.com/2015/12/17/mls-combine-expected-to-raise-the-level-of-local/|publisher=The Saint Kitts and Nevis Observer|accessdate=18 December 2015}}</ref>
